      "text": "The vector 𝐭 together with the matrix 𝐀 may be considered an expanded form of the public key. The vector 𝐭 is compressed in the actual public key by dropping the 𝑑 least significant bits from each coefficient, thus producing the polynomial vector 𝐭 1 . This compression is an optimization for performance, not security. The low-order bits of 𝐭 can be reconstructed from a small number of signatures and, therefore, need not be regarded as secret.\n\nThe ML-DSA public key 𝑝𝑘 is a byte encoding of the public random seed 𝜌 and the compressed polynomial vector 𝐭 1 .\n\nThe ML-DSA private key 𝑠𝑘 is a byte encoding of the public random seed 𝜌 , a private random seed 𝐾 for use during signing, a 64-byte hash 𝑡𝑟 of the public key for use during signing, the secret polynomial\n\n7 In some cases, it is permiss…(truncated)"
